description:
Here is another fine example of why I love my job so much. This passed Wednesday, June 20th, 2012. I had the privilege to seat down and have a conversation on camera with two of the greatest smooth jazz artist of our times, Brian Culberson and David Sanborn, Who's without a doubt, is still alive, the most influential contemporary jazz musician in the last 40 years.

This interview and live performance of the song "Maputo" took place in Alexandria, VA, at the legendary BIrchmere Music Hall and was part of their very successful 2012  Dream tour. Which commemorate the 25th Anniversary of David Sanborn and Michael Sembello's song "The Dream" as well Brian Culbertson's new release CD entitle "DREAMS". Which coincidentally has the same title.


THIS VIDEO FEATURES:

DAVID SANBORN - ALTO SAX
BRIAN CULBERTSON - PIANO & TROMBONE
EDDIE MILLER - KEYBOARDS
RICKY PETERSON - KEYBOARDS & VOCALS
RICHARD PATTERSON - BASS
NICKY MOROCH - GUITAR 
CHRIS MISKEL - DRUMS
GENE LAKE - DRUMS
fulltitle: AQUI Y AJAZZ, DAVID SANBORN & BRIAN CULBERTSON THE DREAM TOUR, INTERVIEW PART 1
